The paper deals with the security threats posed by hardware trojans in integrated circuits (ICs) and proposes a game-theoretic framework to analyze the interactions between an attacker and a defender. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper also involves decision-making and optimization, which are key topics in Game Theory (cs.GT) and Software Engineering (cs.SE), respectively. Additionally, the paper deals with hardware design and testing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.GT, cs.SE, cs.ET, and cs.SY.
